{
  "stem": "8784.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were working outside of the camp and returning in the evening to the, to the Krakau-Plaszow camp.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were still exposed to the extreme brutalities.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And, at times, on many occasions, we would stand in the gathering plaza in the Appellplatz, where we would probably be together there every morning or every evening for counting purposes.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And in those, in those gatherings on the, on the Appellplatz, Amon Goth with his cohorts would come out and walk amongst the people.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The inmates, the inmates were-- at this point, we would be froze still, because we-- as soon as Amon Goth would leave his villa, rumor took off, and it filtered right through the ranks of the inmates.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we all stood so still that you could hear a pin drop, even though there were 20,000 people or so standing there.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because of fear, we were absolutely silent, almost afraid to breathe, because he would-- Amon Goth would have a habit of walking by these lines of people and shooting people that they didn't like or lynch people that they-- for one or another reason, as they'd walk by they would do it.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And lynchings were going on at the same time.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And so we were exposed to these things.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But the good news was that in the mornings or in the evenings we would leave that camp and go to work for Oskar Schindler.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We would also hear-- in addition to, to witnessing these shootings and lynchings, we would also hear the many shootings that were going on far away from us.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was a hill not far from where we stood.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And on that hill, they were killing people on a constant basis, practically.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So we would hear these shots ring out.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
